rial Name Type"},{"iri":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type/group","prefLabel":"Group","definition":"The name of a mineralogical group a specimen belongs to. Groups are defined as a set of mineral species with essentially the same crystal structure and composed of chemically similar elements.","broader":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type/formal-name","scheme":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type","schemeLabel":"Geological Material Name Type"},{"iri":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type/historical","prefLabel":"Historical","definition":"An alias of a mineral name used within a historical context or derived from a historical source","broader":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type/alternate-name","scheme":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type","schemeLabel":"Geological Material Name Type"},{"iri":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type/ima-approved-name","prefLabel":"IMA Approved Name","definition":"A mineral name that has received formal approval by the International Mineralogical Association (IMA)","broader":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type/formal-name","scheme":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type","schemeLabel":"Geological Material Name Type"},{"iri":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type/obsolete","prefLabel":"Obsolete","definition":"A name defined in prior standards or classification systems but has since been removed from those authoritative sources. Includes names designated by the International Mineralogical Association as discredited or obsolete.","broader":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type/alternate-name","scheme":"https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-name-type","schemeLabel":"Geological Material Name Type"},{"iri":"https://